
---


@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes and relationships

class User {
    - id: String (unique)
    - name: String
    - email: String
    - dateOfBirth: Date
}

class Account {
    - accountNumber: String (auto-generated, unique)
    - type: String (either "Personal" or "Business")
    - user: User (1-to-1)
}

class PersonalAccount {
    + createFriendRequest()
    + receiveFriendRequest()
}

class BusinessAccount {
    - companyName: String
    - monthlyFee: Double
}

class Page {
    - pageName: String (unique per account)
    - visits: Integer
    - administrator: Account (1-to-many)
}

class AdvertisementPage extends Page {
    - bounceRate: Double
    - clickThroughRate: Double
    - conversionRate: Double
}

class FriendRequest {
    - sender: PersonalAccount
    - receiver: PersonalAccount
    - status: String (e.g., "Pending", "Accepted", "Rejected")
}

' Inheritance
Account <|-- PersonalAccount
Account <|-- BusinessAccount

' Associations
User "1" -- "1" Account : owns
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page : creates
Page "1" -- "1" Account : administered by
PersonalAccount "0..*" -- "0..*" Page : has privilege to
PersonalAccount "0..*" -- "0..*" FriendRequest : sends
PersonalAccount "0..*" -- "0..*" FriendRequest : receives

' Constraints
note right of User
  A user can only have one account.
  Multiple accounts are against ToU.
end note

note right of Account
  Each account must be either personal or business.
  No overlapping account types for a user.
end note

note right of AdvertisementPage
  Special type of page only for business accounts.
  Tracks marketing metrics.
end note

@enduml

---

### 🧾 Explanation of Key Relationships

| Element | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `User` | Central entity with basic info. One user → one account. |
| `Account` | Base class; users can have only one account (either personal or business). |
| `PersonalAccount` | Extends Account. Can send/receive friend requests. |
| `BusinessAccount` | Extends Account. Must specify company name and pays monthly fee. |
| `Page` | Created by an account. Each page has one admin. Name must be unique per account. |
| `AdvertisementPage` | Subtype of Page, specific to Business Accounts. Records marketing metrics. |
| `FriendRequest` | Only between PersonalAccounts. |

